{"article_id":"VS8y0J5fvg0J4B1O","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Donald Trump referred to impeachment proceedings against him as a \" lynching \" in a Tuesday morning tweet ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"sparking condemnation","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"for using such a racially charged word","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"to describe his political predicament .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"The sadism of white men :","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"why America must atone for its lynchings","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"Read more","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"\" So some day , \"","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"the president wrote ,","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"\" if a Democrat becomes president","depth":12},{"id":10,"text":"and the Republicans win the House , even by a tiny margin ,","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"they can impeach the president ,","depth":12},{"id":12,"text":"without due process or fairness or any legal rights .","depth":12},{"id":13,"text":"All Republicans must remember","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"what they are witnessing here -","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"a lynching .","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"But we will WIN ! \"","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"The tweet fit with Trump ' s history of racist remarks and his strategic use of cruelty ,","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"and some saw in it a political strategy .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"The tweet drew a chorus of outrage .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"\" That is one word","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"that no president ought to apply to himself , \"","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"the South Carolina representative James Clyburn , the House majority whip , said on CNN .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"\" I ' m not just a politician ...","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"I ' m a product of the south .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"I know the history of that word . \"","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"The California representative Karen Bass , chairwoman of the Congressional Black Caucus , told CNN","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"Trump ' s \" lynching \" tweet was consistent with his pattern","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"of throwing out \" racial bombs \"","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"to give \" red meat \" to his base","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"when his back is against the wall .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"Kamala Harris","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"( @ KamalaHarris )","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"Lynching is a reprehensible stain on this nation 's history ,","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"as is this President .","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"We 'll never erase the pain and trauma of lynching ,","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"and to invoke that torture","depth":14},{"id":37,"text":"to whitewash your own corruption","depth":14},{"id":38,"text":"is disgraceful .","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"https : //t.co/XOlsazwwRL","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"\" You think","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"this impeachment is a LYNCHING ? \"","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"tweeted the Illinois representative Bobby Rush .","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"\" What the hell is wrong with you ?","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"Do you know","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"how many people","depth":15},{"id":46,"text":"who look like me","depth":15},{"id":47,"text":"have been lynched , since the inception of this country , by people","depth":15},{"id":48,"text":"who look like you .","depth":15},{"id":49,"text":"Delete this tweet . \"","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"\" Lynching is a reprehensible stain on this nation ' s history ,","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"as is this president , \"","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"wrote presidential candidate and California senator Kamala Harris .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"\" We ' ll never erase the pain and trauma of lynching ,","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"and to invoke that torture","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"to whitewash your own corruption","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"is disgraceful . \"","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"The New Jersey senator and 2020 hopeful Cory Booker tweeted :","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"\" Lynching is an act of terror","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"used to uphold white supremacy .","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"Try again . \"","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"Even Senate majority leader Mitch McConnell , a stalwart Trump ally , said","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"the president had spoken poorly .","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"\" Given the history in our country","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"I would not compare this to a lynching , \"","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"McConnell told reporters on Capitol Hill .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"\" That was an unfortunate choice of words . \"","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"Some elected officials defended Trump .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"Senator Tim Scott , the sole African American Republican in Congress apart from one retiring representative , is from South Carolina .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"According to a report by the Equal Justice Initiative ,","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"between 1877 and 1950 , 184 African Americans were lynched there .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"\" There ' s no question","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"that the impeachment process is the closest thing to a political death row trial ,","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"so I get his absolute rejection of the process , \"","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"Scott said .","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"\" I wouldn ' t use the word lynching . \"","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"The White House claimed","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"Trump had used the word innocently .","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"\" The president has used many words , all types of language ,","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"to talk about the way","depth":14},{"id":80,"text":"the media has treated him , \"","depth":14},{"id":81,"text":"said deputy press secretary Hogan Gidley .","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"\" The president wasn ' t trying to compare himself to the horrific history in this country at all . \"","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"But others saw a clear and familiar political play .","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"\" When the polls get tough ,","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"Potus turns to race , \"","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"tweeted Julian Zelizer , a historian at Princeton University .","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"\" Lynching ? ! \"","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"tweeted the New York Time columnist Charles Blow .","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"\" Sir , don ' t you DARE invoke the darkness of America ' s viciousness toward black people","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"to defend your corruption .","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"How dare you ? ! ... \"","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"According to the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"( NAACP ) ,","depth":14},{"id":94,"text":"from 1882 to 1968 , \" 4,743 lynchings \"","depth":15},{"id":95,"text":"- that is , extrajudicial murders -","depth":15},{"id":96,"text":"\" occurred in the United States .","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"Of these people","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"that were lynched","depth":14},{"id":99,"text":"3,446 were black . \"","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"\" These numbers seem large ,","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"but it is known that not all of the lynchings were ever recorded . \"","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"\" I ' ve studied lynching for decades , \"","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"wrote Sherrilyn Ifill , president of the NAACP legal defense and educational fund .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"\" Read hundreds of lynching accounts .","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"Viewed almost scores of photographs .","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"Wrote a book about lynching .","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"Mr Trump ' s actions & words are consistent w/those","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"who incited lynching , not its victims .","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"And that fact makes this tweet particularly grotesque . \"","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"Carol Anderson , a professor of African American studies at Emory University , confronted Trump with a tweet","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"evoking the horrifying torture","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"enacted on lynching victims .","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"\" You weren ' t castrated & forced to eat your genitalia like Claude Neal , \"","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"Anderson wrote .","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"\" You weren ' t dragged behind a car ,","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"doused w/gasoline","depth":15},{"id":117,"text":"& set on fire like Cleo Wright .","depth":15},{"id":118,"text":"You weren ' t blow torched","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"until your eyes popped out of your head like John Jones .","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"That ' s lynching ... \"","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"America ' s first lynching memorial and museum was opened in Montgomery , Alabama , last year .","depth":5},{"id":122,"text":"Play Video 7:02","depth":3},{"id":123,"text":"Pain and terror :","depth":4},{"id":124,"text":"America remembers its past - video","depth":4},{"id":125,"text":"The impeachment inquiry","depth":6},{"id":126,"text":"being run by Democrats","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"who control the House","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"centres on Trump ' s attempts","depth":5},{"id":129,"text":"to get Ukraine to investigate his political rivals .","depth":4},{"id":130,"text":"How white Americans used lynchings","depth":4},{"id":131,"text":"to terrorize and control black people","depth":4},{"id":132,"text":"Read more","depth":3},{"id":133,"text":"Article I of the US constitution grants the House \" the sole power of impeachment \"","depth":5},{"id":134,"text":"and Article II states","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"that the president \" shall be removed from Office on Impeachment for , and Conviction of , Treason , Bribery , or other high Crimes and Misdemeanors \" .","depth":6},{"id":136,"text":"Lindsey Graham , the other South Carolina senator , said","depth":6},{"id":137,"text":"the process of impeachment against Trump \" is a lynching in every sense \" .","depth":6},{"id":138,"text":"Steve Vladeck , a law professor at the University of Texas , answered with \" a non-exhaustive list of key senses","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"in which impeachment is not a lynching \" .","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"\" 1 ) It is not racially motivated .","depth":7},{"id":141,"text":"2 ) It is a legal process","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"expressly set forth in the text of the constitution .","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"3 ) It doesn ' t result in death of person","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"being lynched . \"","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":289,"left":269,"right":288,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":269,"left":266,"right":268,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":266,"left":150,"right":265,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":148,"right":149,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":0,"right":147,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":1,"right":146,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":265,"left":174,"right":264,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":174,"left":6,"right":173,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":173,"left":162,"right":172,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":162,"left":161,"right":19,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":159,"right":160,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":155,"right":158,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":155,"left":151,"right":154,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":151,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":152,"right":153,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":152,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":153,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":